29/10/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A ceremony launching a joint military exercise takes place Monday (October 29th) at the training centre Pepeliste. The exercise will bring together Special Forces from Macedonia, Albania and Croatia as part of training and co-operation within the Adriatic Charter group. The goal is for the three armies to train for the implementation of joint operations led by NATO. They will be conducted according to NATO standards and evaluated by representatives of the Alliance. Representatives of the armed forces of Bosnia and Herzegovina, Montenegro and Serbia will participate as observers. (Makfax, MIA, Focus - 29/10/07)
